To achieve a "smart" location search feature, you can use the npm package `fuzzball`, which is a text string fuzzy matching library. This helps you compare user inputs with the real location names and return the most closely matched location. First, you need to install the package using:

```
npm install fuzzball
```

Then, you can import it in your app.js:

```javascript
const fuzzball = require("fuzzball");
```

Now, create a function to handle the location matching:

```javascript
const locationNames = ["Москва", "Санкт-Петербург"]; // Add your standardized location names here.

function normalizeLocationName(userInput) {
  const matches = fuzzball.extract(userInput, locationNames, { returnObjects: true });
  const bestMatch = matches.sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score)[0];

  return bestMatch.choice || userInput;
}
```

In this function, we use fuzzball's extract method to get the matching score of each location in `locationNames`. It then sorts and finds the best matching location name. If it doesn't find a good match, it returns the original user input.

Now when registering a new musician, normalize the location input:

```javascript
app.post("/register", (req, res) => {
  // ...
  const newMusician = {
    // ...
    location: normalizeLocationName(req.body.location),
    // ...
  };
  // ...
});
```

In the search functionality, you can filter by location:

```javascript
